NXT (FB8)
.BR
NEXt (FB8)
.BL
When the program is confused as to  which  track-segment  to
choose,  NXT  will  choose  the next segment from the list.
Also see ONE and HOP.
.BL
2 FUM
.BR
This is a macro component.
.BL
2 RET
.BR
This is a macro component.
.BL
2 LOOp
.BR
LOOp the current feature prior to acceptance. The last point is
joined to the first point and the feature becomes closed.
.BL
2 SQUare
.BR
SQUare the current feature prior to acceptance. This facility
is intended for demonstration purposes only as
it has two major drawbacks:
.LM+3
.P-3
a)#The algorithm is only capable of forcing lines parallel
or perpendicular. Any 45 degree lines (e.g. bay windows) will
be forced one way or the other.
.P-3
b)#Squaring is carried out in 'HRD space', which is itself not
square. Hence a four-sided object will be forced into a parallelogram
rather than a rectangle.
.LM-3
.BL
The parameter SQT (q.v.) is used to distinguish between
parallel and perpendicular lines.
.BL
The SQUare command should not be confused with the 'square
feature flag' available in main mode (FB11). The latter command
merely sets a bit in the IFF file to say that a feature
should (or should not) be squared by some suitable post-processor.
.BL
